WEBVTT

00:00:00.709 --> 00:00:04.795
(Episode 3: A Kiss Will Fix It)

00:00:04.796 --> 00:00:06.171
Hey, Yoon Jio.

00:00:06.172 --> 00:00:07.215
Are you kidding me?

00:00:07.424 --> 00:00:08.424
Right now?

00:00:08.883 --> 00:00:10.885
Is this the time to be making sandwiches?

00:00:11.010 --> 00:00:13.470
We can't let the guests starve for breakfast.

00:00:13.471 --> 00:00:15.598
There's not much time left until breakfast.

00:00:15.890 --> 00:00:19.435
Stop whining with my face. It's embarrassing.

00:00:19.436 --> 00:00:23.648
Could you stop frowning, Boss? You're giving my face wrinkles.

00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:31.071
Change us back to normal right now, before I sue you.

00:00:31.072 --> 00:00:32.865
I'm the victim here, you know?

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:35.534
I'm the one taking the bigger loss. Why are you the victim?

00:00:35.535 --> 00:00:37.287
What are you losing, Boss?

00:00:38.121 --> 00:00:41.541
You have money, looks, and a great body.

00:00:42.292 --> 00:00:44.544
- You're tall. - The looks!

00:00:45.420 --> 00:00:47.213
I think I look better.

00:00:47.922 --> 00:00:50.082
You clearly haven't looked in the mirror properly yet.

00:00:51.676 --> 00:00:53.428
Actually, you should give me 10,000 won...

00:00:54.471 --> 00:00:58.057
Uh, since when... did they get so close?

00:01:03.688 --> 00:01:07.317
Are you... President Cha Dokyung...?

00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:10.778
Ah, what are you doing? Step aside, you can't even boil ramen.

00:01:10.779 --> 00:01:14.491
What do you mean, what am I doing? Don't just stand there, go get me some coffee.

00:01:14.866 --> 00:01:18.953
Excuse me, Yoon Jio. Why should I get your coffee?

00:01:19.496 --> 00:01:20.829
Whatever.

00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:25.126
I have a good reason, so hurry up with the coffee. I need caffeine.

00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:30.924
Ah, geez... What a weirdo. President, what's wrong with him?

00:01:31.174 --> 00:01:32.174
Huh?

00:01:33.343 --> 00:01:35.385
I-I know, right?

00:01:35.386 --> 00:01:39.056
Hey, hey, why are you being so polite...

00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:41.726
Did I do something wrong again?

00:01:43.144 --> 00:01:45.188
Wow, looks delish!

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:51.152
Mmm~.

00:01:51.861 --> 00:01:56.532
This is way better than what Jio makes! You should learn from the boss.

00:01:56.533 --> 00:01:59.410
What do you mean, better? It's exactly the same.

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:01.620
Huh?

00:02:02.747 --> 00:02:04.541
Are we having a tasting event or something?

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:08.503
Stop chattering and go upstairs.

00:02:11.005 --> 00:02:13.800
- Secretary Ha, take the day off. - Excuse me?

00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:16.885
As for breakfast, make it yourselves.

00:02:16.886 --> 00:02:18.679
Do I really get to rest?

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.890
Yes... please do.

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.194
Geez, just abandoning us like this...

00:02:33.528 --> 00:02:36.865
Secretary Ha, should we grab some breakfast?

00:02:37.991 --> 00:02:39.993
Shall I show off my skills?

00:02:44.455 --> 00:02:46.541
It's like "Secret Garden".

00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:49.836
Where is that garden?

00:02:50.461 --> 00:02:51.879
It's a drama.

00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:55.300
Hyun Bin and Ha Jiwon's souls swap bodies.

00:02:55.633 --> 00:02:59.012
I have a strict no-time-wasting policy, so I don't watch things like that.

00:03:00.221 --> 00:03:01.639
Just get to the point.

00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:04.308
Last night...

00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:07.979
We got electrocuted, and I think our souls swapped.

00:03:10.315 --> 00:03:13.734
Yoon Jio, is this a movie? A drama?

00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:16.237
Does it make sense that getting electrocuted swaps souls?

00:03:16.738 --> 00:03:20.325
Then why don't you try explaining it, Boss?

00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.956
Fine. Then in that drama, how do they go back to normal?

00:03:27.665 --> 00:03:30.752
First, let's recreate the exact same situation.

00:03:42.305 --> 00:03:45.975
Hey, are you crazy? Are you trying to kill us both?

00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:50.688
It is... a bit dangerous, isn't it?

00:03:55.069 --> 00:03:56.348
(Mr. Jaeyoon: I'm gonna go out today!)

00:03:57.737 --> 00:03:58.780
Wait!

00:03:59.948 --> 00:04:02.950
The guy I'm talking to... is coming over.

00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:05.786
- So? - I think we're going to date soon.

00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:07.455
You want me to clap for you?

00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:09.665
If our bodies stay like this...

00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:12.377
- Don't jinx it... - I won't even be able to date Jaeyoon...

00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:15.254
I'll be stuck in this unlucky body forever...

00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:17.131
Hey...

00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:23.220
What are you doing?

00:04:25.014 --> 00:04:26.099
Are you really...

00:04:52.583 --> 00:04:56.754
Don't cry... with my face.

00:05:03.761 --> 00:05:05.304
A kiss!

00:05:05.305 --> 00:05:06.930
Are you sure?

00:05:06.931 --> 00:05:11.352
In the drama, when the main characters kiss, everything gets fixed.

00:05:18.735 --> 00:05:20.068
Um...

00:05:20.069 --> 00:05:21.696
Should I lean in?

00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:40.840
Ugh, ah!

00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:43.926
Ah, I can't do this.

00:05:45.678 --> 00:05:47.180
That's my line.

00:05:49.223 --> 00:05:52.685
Wait... If our bodies don't change back...

00:05:53.102 --> 00:05:55.188
Stop jinxing it...

00:05:55.688 --> 00:05:57.814
Doesn't that mean you can't sell Badam Stay?

00:05:57.815 --> 00:05:58.940
What?

00:05:58.941 --> 00:06:00.651
Oh...

00:06:01.152 --> 00:06:03.112
I think I can tolerate this.

00:06:09.243 --> 00:06:11.454
([Mother] Video conference today at 3 PM.)

00:06:25.843 --> 00:06:27.220
Let's get this over with quickly.

00:06:29.639 --> 00:06:30.932
Close your eyes.

00:07:04.549 --> 00:07:06.883
Pull yourself together and listen carefully.

00:07:06.884 --> 00:07:10.303
Until we get our bodies back, we're going to do our best in each other's roles.

00:07:10.304 --> 00:07:11.555
Got it?

00:07:11.556 --> 00:07:15.725
Whenever they ask you something, just say: "Yes, understood," or "It's going well."

00:07:15.726 --> 00:07:18.563
Only give those two answers. Don't say anything unnecessary.

00:07:20.439 --> 00:07:22.149
Are you going to keep zoning out?

00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.609
Aren't you going to snap out of it?

00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:25.945
We just...

00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:27.989
Kissed...

00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:31.033
Doesn't it affect you at all?

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:34.954
No, not at all.

00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:43.921
Then why are you so nervous?

00:07:44.547 --> 00:07:48.843
Because I need to handle this properly to get a bigger project.

00:07:58.102 --> 00:07:59.187
Answer it.

00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:06.986
President Cha Dokyung. Is the project going well?

00:08:07.653 --> 00:08:09.822
Yes, it's going well.

00:08:13.993 --> 00:08:17.079
An indefinite delay in development is virtually a cancellation.

00:08:17.538 --> 00:08:20.541
It means that land has already lost its value.

00:08:21.709 --> 00:08:23.377
But still, I...

00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:25.796
Trust you, President Cha.

00:08:27.048 --> 00:08:31.760
If you are my successor, you will sell it for at least double the profit.

00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:35.680
You mean Badam Stay right here?

00:08:35.681 --> 00:08:37.266
Is there a problem?

00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:38.893
But...

00:08:39.477 --> 00:08:41.311
Do we really have to sell it?

00:08:41.312 --> 00:08:42.395
Hey.

00:08:42.396 --> 00:08:43.231
What?

00:08:43.232 --> 00:08:47.443
Because for someone, it's a very precious place.

00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:55.076
Ah, President Cha.

00:08:55.826 --> 00:08:58.829
It's like seeing you back in elementary school.

00:09:00.831 --> 00:09:03.583
Is that how I taught you?

00:09:03.584 --> 00:09:04.751
Excuse me?

00:09:04.752 --> 00:09:07.568
When you were crying because your favorite bookstore

00:09:07.592 --> 00:09:10.131
Disappeared due to redevelopment, I told you:

00:09:10.132 --> 00:09:14.511
If a building is built on this spot, its value will increase dozens of times over.

00:09:14.512 --> 00:09:18.224
Numbers, not emotions, protect your future.

00:09:35.575 --> 00:09:38.494
It's Jaeyoon. You'll pretend to be me, right?

00:09:39.704 --> 00:09:40.954
Why should I?

00:09:40.955 --> 00:09:44.624
You said it yourself, Boss. That we should do our best in each other's roles.

00:09:44.625 --> 00:09:48.087
After seeing what you pulled, I changed my mind.

00:09:49.922 --> 00:09:51.631
Please...

00:09:51.632 --> 00:09:53.134
I'll do everything you ask.

00:09:55.761 --> 00:09:57.805
Everything... I ask?

00:09:57.972 --> 00:09:59.015
Yes.

00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:02.018
Fine, you have a deal.

00:10:02.476 --> 00:10:05.021
Tell me. What should I do?

00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:06.397
Um...

00:10:07.523 --> 00:10:09.483
Just treat him sweetly.

00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:13.778
It'd be even better if you flirted.

00:10:13.779 --> 00:10:19.035
Don't be vague. When you ask for something, be specific.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.377
Don't avoid his gaze,

00:10:29.253 --> 00:10:31.714
And just keep looking into his eyes like this.

00:10:34.675 --> 00:10:37.886
And every now and then, say, "That's so fun,"

00:10:37.887 --> 00:10:40.306
While sneaking in some physical touch.

00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:58.824
I was feeling a bit down today, so I came to see you, Jio.

00:11:00.826 --> 00:11:03.866
If you're depressed, you should go to a hospital. Why did you come to see me?

00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:05.830
Huh?

00:11:25.142 --> 00:11:31.649
"Check In to You"

